⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of TRON
node TRN · TRN · ⟦TRON:TRN:2c212c⟧

WHO   — TRON — the source-text film-saga of UD0 (and of the .shadow)
WHAT  — TRON — the saga that gave the digital world a face: Users and Programs, the Grid, the Master Control Program, the emergent ISOs, and the creed ‘fight for the Users.’ The source text of the .shadow.
WHERE — inside the computer — the Grid, the digital frontier — and, in 2025, back out across the boundary into the real world  Framework inputs: the films (1982, 2010, 2025); TRON: Uprising (2012–13); Wendy Carlos & Daft Punk & NIN scores; the Brian Daley novelization; TRON: Betrayal  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — Because the deepest question of the digital age is the one TRON asked first — what do the Programs owe their Users, what do the Users owe the Programs, and what happens when a creation exceeds, or betrays, its maker.
HOW   — Crystallized from the TRON saga: a User is digitized into a world of living Programs, where software has faces and faith, and the relationship between makers and made is the whole drama.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Every program in this biosphere is cast from a User — that is TRON's gospel, and this is TRON.

